      proof: 'f(c) = S(c) + κ(c) = −c ln c − (1−c)ln(1−c) + ln c. Differentiating: f′(c) = ln((1−c)/c) + 1/c. Setting f′(c) = 0 gives ln((1−c)/c) + 1/c = 0, solved numerically by bisection (see frozen_contract.py) to c* ≈ 0.7822.',
      symbols: ['S', 'κ'],
      domains: ['gcd'],
      related: ['B6', 'B10', 'B9'],
      latin: 'Punctum Fixum Logisticum',
      verification: 'sampled',
    },
    {
