      bounds: 'For all c ∈ (0,1): f(c) + f(1−c) = 0 exactly. Verified across 10,000 points to < 10⁻¹⁵.',
      range: 'f(c) ∈ (−∞, ∞). f(c) > 0 for c > ½, f(c) < 0 for c < ½, f(½) = 0.',
      proof: 'f(c) = S(c) + κ(c) = −(1−c)ln(1−c) + c ln c + ... Substituting 1−c and adding yields cancellation by the symmetry of the Bernoulli entropy.',
