      domains: ['gcd'],
      related: ['E4', 'B7', 'E6'],
      latin: 'Formula Reflexionis',
      verification: 'narrative',
    },
    {
      id: 'B10', series: 'B', name: 'Fisher Space Partition', formula: '63.1% + 24.4% + 12.5% = 100%',
      cluster: 'Fixed-Point Triangle',
      description: 'Collapse/Watch/Stable partition of the Fisher manifold.',
      bounds: 'Stable: 12.5%, Watch: 24.4%, Collapse: 63.1%. Computed by Monte Carlo sampling (10⁶ points) with the four-gate criterion. Stability is rare.',
      range: 'The partition exhausts the full manifold. No overlap between regimes.',
      proof: 'Monte Carlo: draw 10⁶ random trace vectors, compute kernel, classify regime. The partition fractions converge to these values as sample size → ∞.',
      symbols: ['F', 'ω', 'S', 'C'],
      domains: ['gcd', 'finance', 'evolution', 'consciousness_coherence'],
      related: ['B6', 'B8', 'D4', 'D5'],
      latin: 'Partitio Spatii Fisher',
      verification: 'sampled',
    },
    {
      id: 'B11', series: 'B', name: 'Super-Exponential Convergence', formula: 'IC → F faster than e^(-n)',
      cluster: 'Perturbation Chain',
      description: 'IC approaches F super-exponentially fast as channels homogenize. Gap shrinks 28.5×.',
      bounds: 'For n identical channels approaching c₀: Δ(n) ∝ exp(−n·g(c₀)) where g > 1. The 28.5× factor is for n: 4→8 with c₀ = 0.7.',
      range: 'Convergence rate depends on c₀. Fastest near c = 1, slowest near c = ½.',
      proof: 'From the CLT: σ² → 0 as n → ∞ for i.i.d. channels. IC = F·exp(−σ²/(2F²) + ...) and σ² = O(1/n) gives Δ = O(1/n), but the actual convergence is super-exponential due to higher-order corrections.',
      symbols: ['IC', 'F', 'Δ'],
      domains: ['gcd'],
      related: ['B5', 'D2', 'D7'],
      latin: 'Convergentia Super-Exponentialis',
      verification: 'narrative',
    },
    {
      id: 'B12', series: 'B', name: 'Low-Rank Closures', formula: '5 diagnostics → 4 effective dims',
      cluster: 'Composition Algebra',
      description: 'The closure algebra is low-rank — PCA confirms half the DOF are constrained.',
      bounds: '246 closure modules diagnostics (F, IC, S, C, Δ) span only 4 effective dimensions. PCA eigenvalue ratio λ₅/λ₁ < 0.01.',
      range: 'Effective dimensionality: 4 out of 5. The constraint S ≈ f(F,C) removes one DOF.',
      proof: 'The statistical constraint corr(C,S) → −1 as n → ∞ means S is asymptotically determined by F and C. This reduces 5 diagnostics to 4 independent degrees.',
      symbols: ['F', 'IC', 'S', 'C'],
      domains: ['gcd'],
      related: ['E8', 'D7', 'D8'],
      latin: 'Clausurae Rangi Inferioris',
